1
00:01:41,759 --> 00:01:45,520
At first, when I told fortunes for people,

2
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:47,840
business was very bad.

3
00:01:48,720 --> 00:01:50,960
No one believed what I said.

4
00:01:51,960 --> 00:01:56,280
Later, I pretended to be blind and set up a fortune-telling stall.

5
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:59,440
Business was surprisingly good.

6
00:02:00,360 --> 00:02:03,480
Everyone believed what a blind man said.

7
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:07,200
They figured, since you're already blind,

8
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:09,440
you wouldn't lie to me.

9
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,840
Some generous customers

10
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:16,720
would sometimes give me an extra copper coin or two.

11
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:19,680
People are really strange,

12
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:21,440
aren't they?

13
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:28,040
I make more money with my eyes closed than open.

14
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:33,880
You kill so cleanly.

15
00:02:33,960 --> 00:02:37,760
The man fell into the water before he could even react.

16
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:42,680
Even the coroner couldn't find out anything.

17
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:45,920
You are truly a master.

18
00:03:03,640 --> 00:03:05,000
This is all I have.

19
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,440
Enough.

20
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:14,680
I'll come back next month.

21
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:17,130
Didn't you say this was all you wanted?

22
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:23,680
I mean,

23
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:27,640
I want this much every month from now on.

24
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:29,200
Every month.

25
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:32,840
What else? Did you think I was easy to get rid of?

26
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:34,800
I'm not blind.

27
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:38,360
Wait.

28
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:41,720
I'll give you next month's too.

29
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,600
Don't come back next month.

30
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:45,280
All right.

31
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:10,360
Why must I alone drink the bitter wine of this world?

32
00:04:22,880 --> 00:04:24,280
There is one more copy.

33
00:04:24,720 --> 00:04:25,880
Bring it here.

34
00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:29,360
Here.

35
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:34,159
This is too much.

36
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:38,040
It's been too long.

37
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:40,240
It's a bit blurry.

38
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:54,800
Found it.

39
00:04:57,680 --> 00:04:59,400
Patient Xia Chunyi,

40
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:01,320
twenty years old,

41
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:03,320
a native of Luoyang.

42
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:05,600
She once gave birth to a mentally disabled child

43
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:07,800
and worries about the health of her future offspring.

44
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:09,440
She had a child?

45
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:13,560
I never heard her mention it.

46
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:22,680
Xia Cai,

47
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:25,240
male, nearly three years old, from Luoyang.

48
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:26,370
Mentally deficient

49
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:28,080
and appears foolish.

50
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:31,960
Xia Cai.

51
00:05:32,159 --> 00:05:33,760
Xia Cai.

52
00:05:36,120 --> 00:05:37,560
Ah Cai.

53
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:40,400
Do you like it, Ah Cai?

54
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:42,640
This is called a Longevity Pendant.

55
00:05:42,640 --> 00:05:44,720
Your name is engraved on it.

56
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:47,880
Did the couple ever keep a dog?

57
00:05:47,960 --> 00:05:49,520
Yes, they did have one.

58
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:52,600
At that time, Xia Zhiming used to complain about buying goat milk for it every day.

59
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:55,800
He said he'd rather use the money to gamble and win it back.

60
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,440
Where did you take Ah Cai?

61
00:06:02,520 --> 00:06:04,320
Stop pulling me. I sold him.

62
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:06,480
Sold him?

63
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:08,600
Where did you sell him?

64
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,240
The ghost market.

65
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:11,840
Ah Cai!

66
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:15,800
Miss, have you seen a child this tall named Ah Cai?

67
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:17,760
I haven't seen him.

68
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:19,400
Ah Cai!

69
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:22,320
Sir, have you seen a child?

70
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:24,520
Sir, have you seen a child about this tall?

71
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:25,200
Go away!

72
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:26,520
Acai.

73
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:28,640
Acai.

74
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:31,320
Why did you treat him like this?

75
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:34,360
He is your own flesh and blood.

76
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:37,200
He's three years old and still can't speak.

77
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:39,200
He's a fool.

78
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:42,040
I lose so much face outside.

79
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:45,040
When neighbors ask why I buy goat milk,

80
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:47,720
I can only say I have a dog.

81
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:50,720
How dare you hit me?

82
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:52,720
Not only do I dare to hit you,

83
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:55,130
but I will also report to the authorities.

84
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:58,120
Let me go. Why report this to the authorities?

85
00:06:58,120 --> 00:06:59,720
Since you like kids so much,

86
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:01,600
let's have another one, okay?

87
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:03,400
Let me go.

88
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:05,800
Let go.

89
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:08,840
Doesn't murder require a motive?

90
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:11,960
Losing a dog isn't a reason to kill your husband.

91
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:15,000
What exactly is the relationship between this fool and Pan Lang?

92
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:16,440
I asked around.

93
00:07:16,520 --> 00:07:19,680
Pan Lang really did find this fool in the ghost market.

94
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:21,360
Acai.

95
00:07:24,440 --> 00:07:25,840
Acai.

96
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:28,880
Acai.

97
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:45,640
The fool is Chunyi's child.

98
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,120
Hey!

99
00:07:47,320 --> 00:07:48,600
Wait for me!

100
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:51,000
Dad, why is he...

101
00:07:57,000 --> 00:08:00,080
Do you know Master's favorite place to go?

102
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:02,680
The house full of beautiful ladies.

103
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:05,000
You always wait at the door.

104
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:10,640
Master is going to Yichun Pavilion.

105
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:13,920
Master isn't going to spend money this time.

106
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:16,160
He is going to ask the proprietress for money.

107
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:19,360
She gives him whatever food he asks for.

108
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:23,960
Come inside and have fun.

109
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:27,280
Come on, it's been a long time.

110
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:29,480
Come, have a seat, sir.

111
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:45,680
Pan is my master.

112
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:50,120
I know the secret of your husband's death.

113
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:52,360
I saw you kill someone.

114
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:55,520
If you don't pay me, I'll report to the authorities.

115
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:06,760
I'll give it.

116
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:10,000
I'll give it to you.

117
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:14,240
I'll give it.

118
00:10:09,640 --> 00:10:10,920
Acai.

119
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,760
I'm sorry.

120
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:15,760
This longevity pendant isn't silver.

121
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:19,520
But he will never snatch it away again.

122
00:10:25,160 --> 00:10:25,840
Really.

123
00:10:25,920 --> 00:10:27,040
Turn around.

124
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:32,760
I just want you to be healthy,

125
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:34,560
live a long life,

126
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:37,280
and stay by my side forever.

127
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:02,360
Acai.

128
00:11:02,560 --> 00:11:04,880
Acai.

129
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:06,560
Acai.

130
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:09,240
Acai.

131
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:30,960
Acai.

132
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:34,440
I will never leave you again.

133
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:38,960
Wait for me.

134
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:14,560
Step aside.

135
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:27,680
Coroner Li.

136
00:12:55,640 --> 00:12:56,480
What's going on?

137
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:57,120
Wait a minute.

138
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:58,840
What's going on? What happened?

139
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:00,840
There are three bodies inside.

140
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,720
Jueming.

141
00:13:07,840 --> 00:13:09,600
Sister, that little fool...

142
00:13:09,680 --> 00:13:11,940
He is the landlady's own flesh and blood.

143
00:13:31,680 --> 00:13:33,480
Please leave us.

144
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:37,000
I want to be alone with her for a while.

145
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:56,240
I want to see her.

146
00:15:32,680 --> 00:15:34,800
You're a grown man bullying a child.

147
00:15:34,880 --> 00:15:36,080
Aren't you ashamed?

148
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:38,640
Why don't you stay here and do odd jobs?

149
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:40,480
I can't pay you much,

150
00:15:40,560 --> 00:15:42,560
but I can provide food and lodging.

151
00:15:42,640 --> 00:15:43,880
Are you willing?

152
00:15:43,960 --> 00:15:44,960
I'm willing. I'm willing.

153
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:46,360
Thank you, boss.

154
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:49,560
Don't call me boss. Call me Sister Chunyi.

155
00:15:49,680 --> 00:15:51,200
Sister Chunyi.

156
00:16:48,560 --> 00:16:50,000
Chunyi.

157
00:16:55,520 --> 00:16:56,960
I'm sorry.

158
00:16:58,520 --> 00:17:00,240
I'm late.

159
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:04,880
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

160
00:17:07,839 --> 00:17:10,079
I'm an adult too.

161
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:14,520
I can help you.

162
00:17:15,560 --> 00:17:16,960
I can.

163
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:46,320
You are my only family.

164
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,680
I also think of the time

165
00:17:51,760 --> 00:17:53,640
when you saved me,

166
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:58,080
when you took me to see the stars with you,

167
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:03,800
when you gave me mustard porridge.

168
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:14,160
You're so cruel.

169
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:21,400
Only after I left Yichun Brothel did I realize

170
00:18:26,360 --> 00:18:29,600
that life is about constantly losing

171
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:34,480
and constantly gaining.

172
00:18:41,840 --> 00:18:44,360
Sister Chunyi, these are all my books.

173
00:18:44,840 --> 00:18:48,100
I didn't expect you to have so many books at such a young age.

174
00:18:48,320 --> 00:18:49,560
Thank you for taking me in, Sister Chunyi,

175
00:18:49,560 --> 00:18:51,880
so I have a place to keep my books.

176
00:18:53,080 --> 00:18:55,840
If I had a child learning from you,

177
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:57,920
they would surely learn a lot.

178
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:00,260
Do you have any children, Sister Chunyi?

179
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:02,800
I just love children.

180
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:05,960
Whenever I see homeless children, I want to give them a home.

181
00:19:05,960 --> 00:19:08,760
This will be your home from now on.

182
00:19:14,920 --> 00:19:16,780
Sister Chunyi went on a long trip.

183
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:20,520
Before she left, she specifically told me to take good care of you

184
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:22,280
and take you to your new home.

185
00:19:23,280 --> 00:19:25,360
Where are we going?

186
00:19:25,480 --> 00:19:27,680
Yeah, where are we going?

187
00:19:28,760 --> 00:19:29,880
From now on, here,

188
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:31,880
I'll cook for you every day.

189
00:19:31,960 --> 00:19:33,400
What do you like to eat?

190
00:19:34,880 --> 00:19:36,600
Meat. What about you?

191
00:19:37,080 --> 00:19:38,880
Vegetables.

192
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:40,760
Alright, we have everything.

193
00:19:40,960 --> 00:19:43,880
Look, this is your new home.

194
00:19:43,960 --> 00:19:45,240
- Is this okay, Dad?
- Yes.

195
00:19:45,240 --> 00:19:46,520
Look over there.

196
00:19:48,120 --> 00:19:50,240
That's the bed your sister made for you.

197
00:19:50,240 --> 00:19:52,520
This is the new furniture Uncle Su bought for you.

198
00:19:52,520 --> 00:19:53,160
Come sit.

199
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:54,640
So pretty.

200
00:19:54,880 --> 00:19:55,680
Do you like it?

201
00:19:55,720 --> 00:19:56,960
Yes.

202
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:05,440
Catch the thief!

203
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:12,240
Officer,

204
00:20:12,320 --> 00:20:15,120
are you looking for a gift for your sweetheart?

205
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:16,480
You can take a look.

206
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:19,640
I brought all these back from the Western Regions.

207
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:24,000
They have a unique charm when worn.

208
00:20:25,240 --> 00:20:28,000
Here we also have bracelets and jade.

209
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:40,320
Officer, you have great taste.

210
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:43,520
This bracelet is a rare treasure.

211
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:45,600
Let me help you try it on.

212
00:20:47,360 --> 00:20:48,360
Look.

213
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:51,600
The craftsmanship of this bracelet is exquisite.

214
00:20:51,640 --> 00:20:53,160
Its luster is soft,

215
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:54,720
like moonlight.

216
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:57,280
It's the most suitable gift for a beauty.

217
00:20:57,840 --> 00:20:59,680
If you give it to your sweetheart,

218
00:20:59,680 --> 00:21:02,200
it's guaranteed to make her smile.

219
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:05,680
I'll take it. Wrap it up.

220
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:06,760
Okay.

221
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:09,680
Tanghulu! Fresh tanghulu!

222
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:11,080
Take care, Officer.

223
00:21:41,160 --> 00:21:42,720
This must be expensive.

224
00:21:44,640 --> 00:21:46,160
As long as you like it.

225
00:21:47,520 --> 00:21:49,000
I can't keep it here.

226
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:51,280
If my dad finds out...

227
00:21:51,520 --> 00:21:53,960
We can just hide it.

228
00:21:55,480 --> 00:21:56,480
Like this.

229
00:21:57,640 --> 00:21:58,960
There you go.

230
00:22:00,160 --> 00:22:01,280
Honglian,

231
00:22:02,080 --> 00:22:06,720
I want to introduce you to my dad and friends,

232
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:09,720
and tell them we're together.

233
00:22:12,560 --> 00:22:13,680
Honglian.

234
00:22:14,640 --> 00:22:17,040
I hope you can always be this happy.

235
00:22:17,760 --> 00:22:19,800
I will always protect you.

236
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:23,960
Hold on tight.

237
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:28,040
Careful!

238
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:49,840
If she can't make this dish well,

239
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:51,800
I'm really going to starve to death.

240
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:54,720
How many days have I been eating mustard green congee?

241
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:57,720
If I keep eating it, my face will turn green.

242
00:22:58,040 --> 00:22:59,320
It's already the fifth day.

243
00:22:59,320 --> 00:23:01,250
We've been eating it for five days.

244
00:23:03,440 --> 00:23:05,240
My lady, I believe in you.

245
00:23:05,320 --> 00:23:07,280
You can definitely do it.

246
00:23:07,360 --> 00:23:08,360
Yeah.

247
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:10,480
Can you two stop arguing?

248
00:23:10,560 --> 00:23:11,960
I want to focus on making this.

249
00:23:11,960 --> 00:23:13,720
I believe I can make

250
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:16,460
mustard green congee just like the boss lady's.

251
00:23:18,520 --> 00:23:23,480
I think we need to find a way to help her.

252
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:27,240
My lady, I think it's time to add the mushrooms.

253
00:23:27,320 --> 00:23:28,840
Yes, it's about time to add the ingredients.

254
00:23:28,840 --> 00:23:30,900
First, add some shiitake mushrooms.

255
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:35,960
The aroma comes right out once you sprinkle them in.

256
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:39,440
Then add some salt.

257
00:23:43,280 --> 00:23:44,240
Oh no.

258
00:23:44,320 --> 00:23:46,440
I added sugar.

259
00:23:48,040 --> 00:23:48,960
It's fine.

260
00:23:49,040 --> 00:23:51,840
If there's too much sugar, just add some salt

261
00:23:51,920 --> 00:23:54,040
to neutralize it.

262
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:57,960
Add salt for too much sugar, add sugar for too much salt.

263
00:23:57,960 --> 00:23:59,240
Taste it.

264
00:23:59,720 --> 00:24:01,120
See if it's salty enough.

265
00:24:03,720 --> 00:24:04,320
How is it?

266
00:24:04,480 --> 00:24:05,840
Seems pretty good.

267
00:24:05,920 --> 00:24:07,000
Not bad.

268
00:24:07,360 --> 00:24:08,720
Not bad.

269
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:10,240
I don't believe it.

270
00:24:11,040 --> 00:24:15,000
I remember Chunyi said this mustard green porridge is delicious.

271
00:24:15,080 --> 00:24:17,200
Thick but not greasy, with distinct grains.

272
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:21,800
The time and rhythm of stirring are very important.

273
00:24:22,040 --> 00:24:23,920
Keep stirring.

274
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:26,520
Just keep stirring.

275
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:29,720
Stir it,

276
00:24:29,840 --> 00:24:34,800
stir it up, stir it up.

277
00:24:46,200 --> 00:24:47,440
Try it.

278
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:50,600
Try it.

279
00:25:04,960 --> 00:25:07,120
This is the exact flavor.

280
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:13,200
It's exactly the same as Sister Chunyi's.

281
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:15,600
This is the exact flavor.

282
00:25:15,680 --> 00:25:16,560
It's a success.

283
00:25:16,800 --> 00:25:17,720
It's a success.

284
00:25:17,840 --> 00:25:18,760
Thanks to you.

285
00:25:18,840 --> 00:25:21,320
Yeah, my handful of sugar

286
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:22,800
and that handful of salt.

287
00:25:22,800 --> 00:25:24,120
I take credit for it.

288
00:25:24,360 --> 00:25:25,480
Yeah.

289
00:25:32,360 --> 00:25:33,880
Finally, success.

290
00:25:35,600 --> 00:25:37,800
Let's take the mustard green porridge to Jueming.

291
00:25:37,800 --> 00:25:38,800
Okay.

292
00:25:43,640 --> 00:25:44,640
Let's go.

293
00:25:59,480 --> 00:26:03,400
He hasn't gone to the government office or left the house for so many days.

294
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:05,800
We need to find a way to cheer him up.

295
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:07,640
You're right.

296
00:26:08,080 --> 00:26:09,920
But Sulang told me

297
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:11,260
that the proprietress

298
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:13,400
was his last relative.

299
00:26:13,680 --> 00:26:16,800
Now, it's hard for him to accept it at the moment.

300
00:26:18,680 --> 00:26:20,480
We must let him know

301
00:26:20,720 --> 00:26:21,850
that he is not alone.

302
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:22,920
Yes.

303
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:24,160
He still has us.

304
00:26:26,560 --> 00:26:28,400
Oh, kid.

305
00:26:28,520 --> 00:26:30,180
You are writing so seriously.

306
00:26:30,240 --> 00:26:31,680
Uncle An, Sister Jinglan.

307
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:33,160
Look what delicious food I brought for you.

308
00:26:33,160 --> 00:26:34,840
Uncle An, Sister Jinglan.

309
00:26:38,360 --> 00:26:39,440
Mr. Su.

310
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:41,120
Why are you here?

311
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:44,280
We brought some mustard green porridge.

312
00:26:44,280 --> 00:26:45,880
Smells so good.

313
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:47,320
Who made it?

314
00:26:47,560 --> 00:26:49,520
The eldest miss made it.

315
00:26:49,600 --> 00:26:51,160
And your favorite,

316
00:26:52,120 --> 00:26:53,720
shredded pork with green peppers.

317
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:54,560
Your favorite meat.

318
00:26:54,560 --> 00:26:56,640
And scrambled eggs with yellow chives.

319
00:26:56,640 --> 00:26:57,520
Also your favorite.

320
00:26:57,520 --> 00:26:58,240
I want to eat this.

321
00:26:58,240 --> 00:26:59,920
And some fresh green vegetables.

322
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:01,360
Your favorite.

323
00:27:05,840 --> 00:27:07,200
It smells so good.

324
00:27:16,360 --> 00:27:18,400
I made a lot of mustard green congee.

325
00:27:19,640 --> 00:27:22,440
The folks at Yichun Brothel have already had some.

326
00:27:22,520 --> 00:27:24,600
Sit down. Okay, don't worry.

327
00:27:25,120 --> 00:27:26,840
Sit down, sister.

328
00:27:26,960 --> 00:27:28,240
Thank you.

329
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:30,320
Eat.

330
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:34,000
Thank you. Why the long face?

331
00:27:34,080 --> 00:27:35,360
Come on, eat.

332
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:41,560
Now that Yichun Brothel is managed by Mingzhu,

333
00:27:41,680 --> 00:27:43,680
they still have a place to stay.

334
00:27:44,040 --> 00:27:45,160
Rest assured.

335
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:54,360
The young lady practiced making this congee for days.

336
00:27:54,480 --> 00:27:56,600
She finally got it right.

337
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:59,160
Does it taste the same as before?

338
00:27:59,440 --> 00:28:00,640
It's delicious.

339
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:03,400
Thank you.

340
00:28:05,280 --> 00:28:06,960
Don't be too sad.

341
00:28:07,640 --> 00:28:09,920
If the boss lady is watching from heaven,

342
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:13,080
she surely wouldn't want you to be so depressed.

343
00:28:13,880 --> 00:28:16,140
If she knew you blame yourself every day,

344
00:28:16,200 --> 00:28:18,360
it would break her heart.

345
00:28:18,520 --> 00:28:19,920
I am not blaming myself.

346
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:21,600
Such delicious food.

347
00:28:22,040 --> 00:28:23,000
Right?

348
00:28:23,080 --> 00:28:25,880
We all hope you can pull yourself together

349
00:28:25,960 --> 00:28:27,960
and live a good life.

350
00:28:30,400 --> 00:28:33,120
Eat up. Don't you usually smile a lot?

351
00:28:33,200 --> 00:28:34,000
Eat up, eat up.

352
00:28:34,080 --> 00:28:35,200
Okay, let's eat.

353
00:28:35,280 --> 00:28:37,160
Let me get you another bowl of porridge.

354
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:40,680
By the way, you've already solved five cases for us.

355
00:28:41,960 --> 00:28:43,280
According to the agreement,

356
00:28:43,280 --> 00:28:45,360
this house is yours.

357
00:29:22,160 --> 00:29:23,520
Thank you.

358
00:29:42,600 --> 00:29:44,000
It will be okay.

359
00:29:48,040 --> 00:29:49,160
Let's eat.

360
00:29:49,360 --> 00:29:50,160
Dig in.

361
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:52,930
It's rare for her ladyship to cook.

362
00:29:58,960 --> 00:30:00,160
Everyone.

363
00:30:01,560 --> 00:30:03,560
I want to introduce someone to you.

364
00:30:03,760 --> 00:30:06,640
She is very special to me.

365
00:30:08,600 --> 00:30:09,960
Her name is Gu Honglian.

366
00:30:10,040 --> 00:30:13,400
She is the one my heart desires.

367
00:30:13,480 --> 00:30:14,600
Really?

368
00:30:15,160 --> 00:30:17,040
You brat, when did this happen?

369
00:30:17,120 --> 00:30:17,800
How come I didn't know?

370
00:30:17,800 --> 00:30:21,000
I'm telling you now, aren't I? It's not too late.

371
00:30:21,360 --> 00:30:22,320
Hello, uncle. Good, good.

372
00:30:22,320 --> 00:30:23,560
Hello there.

373
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:25,320
This girl is so pretty and delicate.

374
00:30:25,320 --> 00:30:26,680
So wonderful.

375
00:30:26,800 --> 00:30:29,520
How did this boy trick you into being with him?

376
00:30:30,160 --> 00:30:32,080
Su Lang has never tricked me.

377
00:30:32,160 --> 00:30:34,120
He is a man of his word.

378
00:30:37,280 --> 00:30:39,160
What a great day today is.

379
00:30:39,560 --> 00:30:42,400
The Matchmaker has tied so many red strings

380
00:30:42,680 --> 00:30:44,840
to this little courtyard.

381
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:47,320
So wonderful.

382
00:30:48,280 --> 00:30:49,720
I have no problem with it.

383
00:30:49,800 --> 00:30:51,240
But you need to find time

384
00:30:51,320 --> 00:30:53,200
to take her back for your mother to meet.

385
00:30:53,200 --> 00:30:55,600
My mother will definitely like her.

386
00:30:55,880 --> 00:30:56,400
Right?

387
00:30:56,720 --> 00:30:58,320
Honglian brought you gifts.

388
00:30:58,800 --> 00:30:59,320
Look.

389
00:30:59,400 --> 00:31:01,680
She made these herself.

390
00:31:02,480 --> 00:31:04,280
Wow.

391
00:31:05,040 --> 00:31:07,560
And us.

392
00:31:08,640 --> 00:31:09,960
This is

393
00:31:10,040 --> 00:31:11,360
Uncle.

394
00:31:11,600 --> 00:31:13,240
This is Sulang.

395
00:31:13,320 --> 00:31:15,400
And this is me.

396
00:31:15,600 --> 00:31:17,480
These are Nianxia and Yichun.

397
00:31:17,720 --> 00:31:18,880
This is Sister Jinglan.

398
00:31:18,880 --> 00:31:20,800
And this one?

399
00:31:20,880 --> 00:31:22,040
It's so beautiful.

400
00:31:22,120 --> 00:31:23,200
How about this?

401
00:31:23,320 --> 00:31:26,480
We'll stick these paper cutouts in our courtyard,

402
00:31:26,560 --> 00:31:29,040
so they can keep you company every day. Okay?

403
00:31:29,120 --> 00:31:30,200
Your crossing paths

404
00:31:30,200 --> 00:31:31,680
is all due to fate.

405
00:31:31,760 --> 00:31:33,760
There's one thing I must tell you.

406
00:31:33,840 --> 00:31:36,600
From today on, your investigation squad

407
00:31:36,680 --> 00:31:38,760
must unite,

408
00:31:38,840 --> 00:31:40,120
work closely together,

409
00:31:40,120 --> 00:31:42,400
and maintain the order of Luoyang City.

410
00:31:42,720 --> 00:31:43,520
Okay, Father.

411
00:31:43,520 --> 00:31:46,640
And don't forget what I always say.

412
00:31:46,760 --> 00:31:48,520
Safety comes first.

413
00:31:48,600 --> 00:31:51,040
Solving cases can wait.

414
00:31:51,200 --> 00:31:53,640
Right, that phrase again.

